============================================================
Problem 1c: Find P(X + Y > 0 | 2X - Y = 0)
============================================================

Parameters:
μ_X = 1, σ²_X = 2
μ_Y = -2, σ²_Y = 3
ρ = -0.666667
Cov(X,Y) = -1.6329931619

Let U = X + Y and V = 2X - Y
μ_U = μ_X + μ_Y = 1 + (-2) = -1
μ_V = 2μ_X - μ_Y = 2(1) - (-2) = 4

Var(U) = σ²_X + σ²_Y + 2Cov(X,Y)
       = 2 + 3 + 2(-1.6329931619)
       = 1.7340136763

Var(V) = 4σ²_X + σ²_Y - 4Cov(X,Y)
       = 4(2) + 3 - 4(-1.6329931619)
       = 17.5319726474

Cov(U,V) = Cov(X+Y, 2X-Y)
         = 2Var(X) - Var(Y) + (2-1)Cov(X,Y)
         = 2(2) - 3 + -1.6329931619
         = -0.6329931619

============================================================
CONDITIONAL DISTRIBUTION: U | V = 0
============================================================

E[U | V = 0] = E[U] + Cov(U,V)/Var(V) * (0 - E[V])
             = -1 + (-0.6329931619/17.5319726474) * (0 - 4)
             = -1 + -0.0361050735 * (-4)
             = -0.8555797058

Var(U | V = 0) = Var(U) - Cov(U,V)²/Var(V)
               = 1.7340136763 - (-0.6329931619)² / 17.5319726474
               = 1.7111594116
σ(U | V = 0) = 1.3081129201

P(U > 0 | V = 0) = P(X + Y > 0 | 2X - Y = 0)
                 = 1 - Φ((0 - -0.8555797058)/1.3081129201)
                 = 1 - Φ(0.6540564600)
                 = 0.2565377156

